  br
  | • You are responsible for resolving payment-card disputes. If a backer of a request you accepted disputes the charge with their card issuer, it is your responsibility to handle re-presenting the charge to settle the dispute with the card issuer.
  br
  br
  | • Don't count your chickens before they hatch. Don't assume you'll be able to accept a request when you want; there could be a reason we're not able to allow you to accept a request, or a problem that takes time to resolve. Don't assume you'll be able to immediately collect your funding; there may be a delay between the acceptance of a request and your access to the funds. And don't take any actions in reliance on collecting any of the money contributed until you actually have the ability to withdraw it from your account and spend it.


